This paper is about 3D object detection using point clouds, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a semi-supervised learning approach, which involves training a model with both labeled and unlabeled data, and this is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of generalization to new and unseen data, which is a topic related to robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a method for enforcing consistency between predicted object proposals, which is a topic related to natural language processing (cs.CL) as well as computer vision.
